section.section:
"Doctoral degree in psychology" means:
A degree received from a program that at the time the degree was awarded:
Is accredited by the American Psychological Association or the Canadian Psychological Association; or
Is listed in the designated doctoral programs in psychology published by the Council for the National Register of Health Service Providers in Psychology; or
A doctoral degree in psychology that the Council for the National Register of Health Service Providers in Psychology determines meets its criteria for a doctoral degree in psychology, if the degree was received from a doctoral program in psychology that:
Is located outside the United States and Canada;
Is currently accredited or designated in accordance with paragraph (1)(i) of this subsection, but was not accredited or designated at the time the degree was awarded;
Was completed prior to 1981 for United States programs;
Was completed prior to 1988 for Canadian programs; or
Is no longer in existence.
